Package metro.algorithm

Class ModelParameters

java.lang.Object
metro.algorithm.ModelParameters
public class ModelParameters
extends java.lang.Object
Class used to specify parameters of the metro simulation: - trains' wagons - trains' routes - initial order - stations
See Also:
Coordinates, FieldTypes

  • Constructor Details

    • ModelParameters

      public ModelParameters​(FieldTypes[] trainOrder)
      Initializes routes to the default values.
      Parameters:
      trainOrder - an array of FieldTypes enum values T1, T2, T3, specifying the initial order of the trains

    • ModelParameters

      public ModelParameters​(FieldTypes[] trainOrder, Coordinates[][] routes)
      Parameters:
      trainOrder - an array of FieldTypes enum values T1, T2, T3, specifying the initial order of the trains
      routes - an array of Coordinates pairs, specifying each route's start and end e.g. For train 1 route routes[0][0] = start, route[0][1] = end For train 2 route routes[1][0] = start, route[1][1] = end
